page.title: 07King's Lynn Fisher Fleet
page.content: There are approximately forty to fifty boats set out from King's Lynn.Twenty of these boats go out all the year round.Sixteen boats catch prawns only.The boats have to go out on the high tide, which can be between twelve midnight and 10.30am. and they have to return twelve hours later on the next high tide. When they return, they are moored in threes and as there is not much room the last in will be first out the following day. {CATCHES Spring}Brown shrimp, skate,cockles {Summer}Brown shrimp, pink shrimp,cockles,crab,sole. {Autumn}Brown shrimp, pink shrimp, cockles,mussels,dogfish. {Winter}Brown shrimp,mussels,sprats herring,cod,and pink shrimps from the Silver pit in the North sea.
